      },
      "date": "2012-08-24 09:35:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(6 inline comments)\n\nMajor issue is the OBD_CONNECT flag conflict, but a number of other issues also exist.\n\nI'm all in favour of improving small IO performance, but at only 2-3% improvement over normal bulk RPCs we have to consider code complexity and maintainability against the minor performance win.\n\nAre there further patches in this series that will improve other parts of the small IO performance?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
